@iravid The issue isn't with the paralell sets, it's with the sets followed by the gets at the end. As @evis points out above, the Java memory model doesn't guarantee that these writes will be observable to the following reads.

Ideally what I would do is have an array of volatile references, however the JVM only allows for volatile references to arrays. The only ways to perform volatile sets/gets on an array in Java are an atomic array or a VarHandle (JVM >= 9). The ARA is used for volatility not atomicity.

I don't think this would ever be a problem on x86 but on an architecture with weak memory consistency (like arm for example) it would be required

